@node Avail

Avail : (File dir/dir.avail)
----------------------------

This is a confusing GUI. It is meant to show you how much memory
is used up by various programs you run. However, it saves the
memory display into a little file in ram, so it does not allways
show it correctly (The difference is about 8 bytes). 

If you want a true memory count, click on "flush" and then on the 
"avail" and "reset" buttons repeatedly, until you get a 0 in both
the displays. Then run the program you want to check and then
click on "avail". The memory used should be displayed correctly.

It helps a lot if you know what you're doing..

@endnode
